summary: This is an internal FBI email exchange from June 27, 2022, between two FBI personnel in the New York Field Office. It discusses logistical coordination regarding a victim specialist named Mandy and access for an individual (potentially a victim or witness) related to the Maxwell case, referencing a list and entry assistance.

persons.name: Mandy
persons.context: Mentioned as the recipient of an email from an FBI Special Agent, discussing coordination for an individual's access the following day.

persons.name: Lam
persons.context: Referenced indirectly as someone who put an unnamed individual on a list, necessitating access assistance from the FBI personnel.

connections.description: Lam placed an individual on a list that Mandy, as a Victim Specialist, is helping to facilitate access for.

events.title: Planned Access Coordination
events.description: An individual, placed on a list by Lam, requires assistance from FBI personnel (Mandy and the Special Agent) to gain entry the following day.

keyFacts: The email is an internal FBI communication dated June 27, 2022, regarding the Ghislaine Maxwell case.
It references logistical coordination for an individual's access, indicating ongoing victim/witness support activities.
A person named 'Lam' is mentioned as having placed an individual on a list, suggesting a procedural or security step.
The correspondence involves an FBI Special Agent from the Child Exploitation/Human Trafficking unit and a Victim Specialist.
